passwordstore.org

pass otp also supports One-Time Passwords

Adding your Gmail TOTP secret:
When you set up 2FA in Gmail, Google shows you a QR code. You need the otpauth:// URI from it. A few ways to get it:

Use a QR decoder on the QR code image (e.g. zbarimg screenshot.png)
Use a browser extension that can read the QR code on screen
In Google Account → Security → 2-Step Verification, some flows let you choose "can't scan" and show the raw secret key

pass otp add email/gmail


pass otp insert email/gmail

pass otp append email/gmail

pass otp email/gmail

pass otp -c email/gmail
```

---

**Storing alongside your password:**

`pass-otp` supports storing the `otpauth` URI in the same file as your password (just as an additional line), so you can keep everything together:
```
yourpassword
otpauth://totp/Gmail:you@gmail.com?secret=YOURSECRETHERE&issuer=Google
